{"sha": "3c22361370f618b2414ff47da2ff9f2d27adb5e1", "node_id": "C_kwDOANBUbNoAKDNjMjIzNjEzNzBmNjE4YjI0MTRmZjQ3ZGEyZmY5ZjJkMjdhZGI1ZTE", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Pierre-Emmanuel Patry", "email": "pierre-emmanuel.patry@embecosm.com", "date": "2023-02-09T09:47:15Z"}, "committer": {"name": "CohenArthur", "email": "arthur.cohen@embecosm.com", "date": "2023-02-14T19:43:16Z"}, "message": "lex: Prevent directories in RAIIFile\n\nRAIIFile constructor was accepting directory filename. This lead to\nunattended directory opening in some part of the code (load_file_bytes)\nwich resulted in ice. Since RAIIFile are used for the lexer, removing\nthe ability to open directories with RAIIFile fixes those issues and\nprevent future mistakes.\n\ngcc/rust/ChangeLog:\n\n\t* lex/rust-lex.h: Add file type check.\n\nSigned-off-by: Pierre-Emmanuel Patry <pierre-emmanuel.patry@embecosm.com>", "tree": {"sha": "0785a2dd8d34a9f5cc06e10ba35d60ef467096d7", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/0785a2dd8d34a9f5cc06e10ba35d60ef467096d7"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/3c22361370f618b2414ff47da2ff9f2d27adb5e1", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/3c22361370f618b2414ff47da2ff9f2d27adb5e1", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/3c22361370f618b2414ff47da2ff9f2d27adb5e1", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/3c22361370f618b2414ff47da2ff9f2d27adb5e1/comments", "author": {"login": "P-E-P", "id": 32375388, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMyMzc1Mzg4", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/32375388?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/P-E-P", "html_url": "https://github.com/P-E-P", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/P-E-P/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/P-E-P/following{/other_user}", "gists_u